	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I was speaking directly in response to how MMC5 PCM had been used in a &quot;recent hack&quot; (which turned out to be infidelity's Mario All-Stars NES compilation hack). I thought this was not a good idea, <s>and apparently so did its author, who changed this in a later revision.</s> (Edit: I think infidelity eventually kept it in, after checking back.)<br /><br />As for Shin-4-Nin Uchi Mahjong, I suppose its use there could have easily been done via the regular APU, but they didn't have to deal with emulators and their lack of support for the hardware feature.<br /><br />If you're writing an emulator, sure, support it. I made an NSF test of it a while back, if it helps.

		
